\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Don't mind what I look like for now. Due to the limited time and budget of this game this is what the programmer has to work with, but that's not what's important.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>So you wanna learn how to cook and compete in this here competition?
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>In order for you to succeed in this competition you need to gather resources and be able to cook it. There are a plethera of items scattered around Gastropolis.

\n<CHEF><WordWrap>I've scattered around a few items here before we can get to the main city.They are hidden inside chests, go near one and if you see an "ENTER" key indicator that means it can be interacted. I want you to get the ingredients and bring them back to me.

Search the small village for items that CHEF has requested
Interact the chests to find the ingredients that CHEF has requested
A new Quest has been added to your log. Press "ESC" to view your quests.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Find the items inside wooden crates. If you find it difficult just go near an object and see it there is an indicator that the object can be interacted.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Come back to me once you found the items.

Search the small village for items that CHEF has requested
Interact the chests to find the ingredients that CHEF has requested
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Great! Now since you have collected the ingredients, now its the time for you to learn how to craft.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>So in order for you to be able to craft food you need recipe's.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Luckily for you I have a spare recipe with me. Here you go.

\n<CHEF><WordWrap>One you have a recipe, open your menu by pressing "ESC" and you will see a crafting option. one you clicked on it, select the "Pandesal" to craft the food. Once you crafted the food give it to me.
Press "ESC" to open menu and select crafting
Press "ENTER" to select the item/recipe you want to view/craft
Press "ENTER" again to select the recipe you want to craft
Press "ESC" to go back or return to the menu page
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Well what are you waiting for? Go around the map and find the ingredients!
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Find the items inside wooden crates. If you find it difficult just go near an object and see it there is an indicator that the object can be interacted.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Come back to me once you found the items.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Well what are you waiting for? Go around the map and find the ingredients!
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Find the items inside wooden crates. If you find it difficult just go near an object and see it there is an indicator that the object can be interacted.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Come back to me once you found the items.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>If you noticed, your EXP level has increased. The more food you find the greater your EXP and the greater chances of you being able to create wonderful dishes increases as well.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>If you ever stumble upon a dish but you are low level, the chances of you being able to create that this is really low. You will be wasting items rather than creating dishes.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>A bit of advice, make sure to level up first or have plentyfull of items before crafting so that you will spend less time on crafting a dish.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>The contest will be riddled with high level dishes, so finding other dishes in order to level up will benefit you greatly.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>And if you're wondering where are the other recipe's, well...you gotta find them around Gastropolis.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>But before we proceed to Gastropolis. I wan't to teach you something very important.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>There are going to be challenges, puzzle's, and minigame's that will prove a hindrance to your progress to Gastropolis.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>I will test you by making you play a minigame right here. Don't worry it won't be too difficulty.

Hit the right buttons displayed on the screen before the timer gauge runs out.
The sequence of the buttons is from left to right.
Make sure to hit the sequence correctly.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Contrats on beating the minigame. This minigame will appear several times in different scenarios and different speeds and difficulty.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Be prepared when facing these types of challenges.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Looks like you are prepared for now...

\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Do you want to go to Gastropolis right now or stay here for now and train a bit more?
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>So you want to go to Gastropolis right now?

\n<CHEF><WordWrap>So looks like you have completed the task I have given you.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Those "tasks" are called Side Quests. They are not a main priority over the main quest but something to do.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Side quests are not mandatory, but if you do decide on completing they will give you various items that will help you.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>But since you now know what to do for the most part, we can now head to Gastropolis.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Follow the path straight ahead and you can reach Gastropolis.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>I'll head first, so see ya there.
